  • 【Upgraded Motion Sensor Closet Light】With its upgraded motion detection technology, this HOKOILN motion sensor closet light will automatically turn on when human motion is detected within a range of 10ft/120° in a dark or low light environment, and will shut off after around 18 seconds of no movement to conserve energy. You can say goodbye to fumbling around and searching for a switch in the dark.
  • 【Eye-Protection & 3 Color Temperatures】Instead of emitting light directly, it is emitted to the side and then reflected onto the light guide plate by a reflector without encountering any glare or video flash. Equipped with 60 energy-saving LEDs coated by a non-glare diffused cover, this motion sensor light indoor is soft and no harm to eyes. Additionally, this motion sensor light is designed with 3 color temperatures. Experience crisp clarity with cool white (6000K), enjoy a harmonious ambiance with neutral white (4000K), or create a cozy atmosphere with warm white (3000K).
  • 【Easy Installation in 2 Seconds】With compact dimensions of 12”*1.57”*0.35” (ultra-thin) and a weight of only 4.5 OZ, this light bar features 2 powerful built-in magnets, allowing for easy attachment to iron surfaces (not suitable for aluminum surfaces). We also provide highly adhesive iron plates. Put them around the magnet markings( on the back of the light bar), they will quickly attached. In this way, you can stick the light bar on anywhere you want. Whether you need to charge the light or relocate it, removal is a breeze. No need for drilling or screwing during installation.
  • 【Fast Type-C Charging & No Battery Waste】Equipped with a grade A+ rechargeable battery, this under cabinet light features a larger capacity compared to others on the market, resulting in longer actual usage time. Thanks to upgraded Type-C fast charge chips, the under cabinet light only takes around 3 hours to fully charge, allowing you to confidently use it for 45 to 60 days (if the light is activated 7-10 times a day). Additionally, our rechargeable battery can also reduce D/C/AA/AAA dry battery waste!
  • 【Wide Application】Multi-functional under counter light, the perfect accessory for both elders and young. Illuminate your space effortlessly with our versatile and easy-to-handle under counter light. Great for the closet, cabinet, kitchen, cupboard, pantry, basement, stairs, hallway, bookshelf, etc. Ensure that the contact surface is kept clean and dry before use and then you can enjoy the convenience of an emergency light wherever you need it most.

    • Neil Colquitt
      5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Great 5 star product
      Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2021
      I love this product! I’ve purchased 3 sets so far and have placed them strategically around my house. I’m an early riser and hate using lights around the house only to have to go behind myself and turn them out. The magnetic base allows me to remove them to replace the... See more
      I love this product! I’ve purchased 3 sets so far and have placed them strategically around my house. I’m an early riser and hate using lights around the house only to have to go behind myself and turn them out. The magnetic base allows me to remove them to replace the batteries. I have both the battery and rechargeable lights but, I like these better in the event of a power outage. I have placed them in closets and hallways and any non-occupied room like bathrooms and spare bedrooms. The light is bright enough to shower with if so needed. The pantry and front and back egress or also great places. I rarely turn on a light anymore and it’s neat to see that they respond quickly and quietly. So long as you’re moving they remain on. So they work great at the coffee pot and under the sink. I’ve only had to change out the battery in a couple of the lights that are used in the hallway and bathrooms. The oldest lights are a couple months old on the original batteries.
      A few cons but nothing to change the 5 star rating.
      I would like to see an upgrade model in the near future. The upgrades would help out on how long the batteries last. First I’d like to be able to adjust the intensity of the light. The hallway and bathrooms do not always need to be brightly lit. Second I’d like to be able to adjust the motion sensor sensitivity. I’d like to use additional lights in areas with some movement, like sitting areas. I’ve tried using them in the bedroom and living room but their sensitivity is so good that any motion sets them off. Third I’d like to be able to adjust their light sensitivity. Some places like the hallway come on even during the day because of low lighting. If you leave a light on they won’t come on but that defeats their purpose. These updates would easily increase the life of the batteries and open up more places that they could be used.

      We have had one of these at our old house for at least ten years. It was in our laundry room, which also served as the access to the rest of our house from the garage. Before this, we had to fumble for a wall switch after dark. That solved the problem very well.
